article.headline: Marist 86, Niagara 68
article.story: POUGHKEEPSIE, N.Y. -- David Devezin scored 23 points and Ryan Schneider had 15 points and 10 rebounds to lead Marist over Niagara 89-68 Sunday in the Metro Atlantic Athletic Conference. Marist (7-11, 3-3) hit 10-of-15 from three-point range for the game and built a 42-23 lead by the half. Tyrone Lewis scored 17 points for Niagara (13-4, 4-1). Bilal Benn added 13 points and nine rebounds. The Purple Eagles sunk only seven of 26 three-point attempts. They were 17-of-56 from the floor, compared to nearly 50 percent shooting by the Red Foxes.
